 **1.1 GitHub Commit History** 
![](data:image/png;base64,)


My repository is organized into three folders: ClientSide, ServerSide, and README.md. The Angular frontend is implemented in ClientSide, and the Node.js backend is in ServerSide. I used only the main branch to avoid merge conflicts and ensure smoother deployment.

The development process was as follows:

1. I created all required models and components to clearly define the structure and files needed.
2. I generated dummy data and implemented core functions such as join/leave group, create group/channel, submit join requests, promote users, etc., depending on the user role.
3. I integrated local storage to maintain user sessions, allowing users to log out and log back in without losing functionality.
4. Finally, I built the backend and connected it with the frontend using Socket.IO and REST API.

**1.3.REST API**

The Angular frontend communicates with the Node.js backend using these REST API routes:

| User Route | Method | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| /api/login | POST | Authenticate a user and return user info. |
| /api/register | POST | Register a new user. Automatically creates join requests for existing groups. |
| /api/users | GET | Retrieve all users. |
| /api/users/:id | GET | Retrieve a specific user by ID. |
| /api/users/:id | DELETE | Delete a user account, remove from groups/channels, and delete join requests. |

| Group Route | Method | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| /api/groups | GET | Retrieve all groups. |
| /api/groups/:id | GET | Retrieve details of a specific group. |
| /api/groups | POST | Create a new group. Adds creator and SUPER_ADMINs automatically. |
| /api/groups/:id | PUT | Modify group details. |
| /api/groups/:id | DELETE | Delete a group, remove channels, users, and join requests. |

| Channel Route | Method | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| /api/groups/:id/channels | GET | Retrieve all channels for a specific group. |
| /api/groups/:id/channels | POST | Create a new channel inside a group. |
| /api/groups/:groupId/channels<br><br>/:channelId | DELETE | Delete a channel from a group. |
| /api/channels | GET | Retrieve all channels across groups. |
| /api/channels/:channelId/<br><br>messages | GET | Retrieve messages for a specific channel. |

| Join Request Route | Method | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| /api/join-requests | GET | Retrieve all pending join requests. |
| /api/groups/:id/join-requests | GET | Retrieve join requests for a specific group. |
| /api/groups/:id/join-requests | POST | Submit a join request for a group. |
| /api/groups/:id/join-requests/:userId/approve | POST | Approve a user's join request, adds user to group. |
| /api/groups/:id/join-requests/:userId/reject | POST | Reject a user's join request. |

| User-Group Route | Method | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| /api/groups/:groupId/users/:userId | DELETE | Remove a user from a group (leave group). |
| /api/groups/:id/users/:userId/promote | POST | Promote a user to GROUP_ADMIN or SUPER_ADMIN. |
| /api/groups/:id/users | GET | Retrieve all users who are members of a specific group. |

****1.4 Angular Architecture****

**Components**

- Dashboard
  - Displays groups which is a user belong to and the other group he may interest in and delete account button for chat user and create group form for admin.
  - Actions: createGroup(), requestJoinGroup(), leaveGroup(), deleteAccount().
- ChannelList
  - Displays channels in a specific group and remove/approve user button and create channel button for group admins promote button for super admin.
  - Actions: openChannel(), createChannel(), deleteChannel().
  - Handles pending requests (approveRequest(), rejectRequest()).
- ChannelChar
  - Displays chat field that messages are displayed, and ban button for group admin.
  - Actions: sendMessage(), BanUser()
- Navbar
  - Handles login/logout and navigation.
  - Alerts user if they try to access restricted pages without login.

**Services**

- UserService
  - Stores current user in memory or session.
  - Provides helper methods: getCurrentUser(), logout(), leaveGroup().
- GroupService
  - Maintains list of groups (with BehaviorSubject for reactive updates).
  - CRUD operations for groups: createGroup(), deleteGroup(), modifyGroup().
- ChannelService
  - Provides channels for a given group.
  - Create and Delete operation and banUserFromChannel()

SocketService

- - Manages Socket.IO connection.
    - Emits and listens for real-time events like groupCreated, requestApproved.
